olive oil
1 packet margherita-style pizza with cherry tomatoes & basil pesto
1 pear
1 bag salad leaves
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Boil the kettle.
• Bake pizzas directly on wire oven racks until cheese is melted and golden, 12-15 minutes.

TIP: Placing the pizzas directly onto the wire racks helps the base to crisp up.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice pear.
• In a medium bowl, combine pear, salad leaves, grated Parmesan cheese and a drizzle of olive oil and balsamic vinegar. Season with salt and pepper.

• Slice margherita pizza.
• Divide margherita pizza, pear and Parmesan salad between plates. Enjoy!